And you allow someone else to dress you. That means the Holy Spirit.

00:14:46.880 --> 00:14:52.320
And take you where your ego doesn't want to go. Well, that's what the spirit typically does.

00:14:52.032 --> 00:14:57.248
Can the spirits leading you to greater love, to greater love, to greater love,

00:14:57.024 --> 00:15:00.352
"'Feed my lambs, feed my sheep, feed my lambs.'

00:15:01.408 --> 00:15:04.864
See, we're all meant to identify here with Peter.

00:15:04.800 --> 00:15:09.344
we've all been sifted by satan. we're all ambiguous characters.

00:15:10.624 --> 00:15:11.808
We need to.

00:15:11.680 --> 00:15:12.896
Say,

00:15:12.768 --> 00:15:15.136
Again and again and again.

00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:16.544
Lord, I love you.

00:15:16.288 --> 00:15:18.784
Lord, I love you. Lord, I love you.

00:15:18.976 --> 00:15:20.160
And then,

00:15:20.032 --> 00:15:22.304
Be willing to feed his sheep

00:15:23.040 --> 00:15:24.992
That's how we become his disciples.

00:15:25.312 --> 00:15:26.560
And God bless you!

00:15:31.712 --> 00:15:35.936
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron.

00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:41.312
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire dot Org.
